{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":30227,"record_hash":"sha256:4912a8114245f5c94a7e9c3fae1438823843b30b5bdf899b251e5487f257374e","timestamp":"2026-05-11T16:47:35.557Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 212984\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1202\nOutput:\n\n## Command Shape\n\nInitial POC command:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog sync [--remote <name>]\n```\n\nWhen `--remote` is omitted, use `origin`.\n\nBehavior:\n\n1. Resolve the GitMeta remote.\n2. Fetch the agentlog metadata ref from that remote.\n3. Materialize fetched agentlog metadata into local GitMeta SQLite.\n4. Serialize local agentlog keys into the agentlog metadata ref.\n5. Push that ref to the remote.\n6. On non-fast-forward push rejection, fetch, materialize, re-serialize, and\n   retry a small bounded number of times.\n\nThe command does not need an agent argument. It operates on stored GitMeta\nagentlog data, not on a live provider transcript.\n\nHuman output can stay terse:\n\n```text\nSynced agentlog metadata with origin\n```\n\nJSON output can mirror that with a simple object. More detailed counters are\nuseful later, but not required for the first lifecycle POC.\n\n## GitMeta API Implication\n\nThe current high-level GitMeta APIs are close but not quite the right shape for\nagentlog-only sync:\n\n- `Session::serialize()` serializes all shareable metadata according to global\n  filter rules.\n- `Session::pull()` fetches and materializes configured metadata refs.\n- `Session::push_once()` pushes the main serialized metadata ref.\n\nUsing those directly would make `but agentlog sync` exchange unrelated metadata\ntoo. That breaks the command's scope.\n\nPrefer a small GitMeta API extension over reimplementing transport in\n`but-agentlog`. The API should let a caller exchange an explicit key scope.\nConceptually:\n\n```text\nserialize only keys matching:\n  gitbutler:agent-sessions\n  gitbutler:agent-session:**\n\nwrite local ref for that scope:\n  refs/meta/local/agentlog\n\nfetch/push the matching remote ref:\n  refs/meta/agentlog\n\nmaterialize only that fetched agentlog ref\n```\n\nExact function names can be decided in `git-meta`, but the important API\nproperty is that key scope is command-scoped, not achieved by mutating the\nuser's persistent `meta:filt\n[TRUNCATED]\n Ordering And Dedupe\n\nRemote materialization can merge metadata from multiple machines. Readers should\nnot depend on stored GitMeta list order. After sync, consumers should:\n\n- dedupe transcript records by `record_hash`\n- sort by `source_key` and `record_index` within one source\n- use `timestamp`, `source_key`, `record_index`, and `record_hash` as stable\n  ordering inputs across multiple sources\n\nThis matches the data model documented in\n[GitMeta Data Model](gitmeta-data-model.md).\n\n## Privacy Posture\n\n`agentlog sync` should be explicit in the first implementation. Captured\ntranscripts are redacted, but they can still reveal sensitive project context,\nprompting strategy, file names inside tool commands, and architectural details.\n\nFuture GitButler UX can decide whether agentlog sync is:\n\n- manual only\n- part of a GitButler \"sync workspace\" action\n- part of branch/PR publish\n- best-effort background sync for opted-in projects\n\nThat policy should live above `but-agentlog`; the crate should provide a small\nsync primitive and clear result reporting.\n\n## Failure Handling\n\nFor the explicit command:\n\n- missing GitMeta remote should fail clearly\n- fetch/materialize failure should fail the command\n- push non-fast-forward should retry after fetch/materialize/re-serialize\n- repeated push failure should fail clearly\n- no remote data and no local changes should succeed with an up-to-date message\n\nFor future integration with normal GitButler push/fetch flows, the product needs\nto decide whether metadata sync failure blocks code sync or is reported as a\nrecoverable warning.\n\n## Decided POC Choices\n\n- `but agentlog sync` is a full bidirectional sync command.\n- Do not add `--push-only` or `--pull-only` until there is a concrete need.\n- If `--remote` is omitted, use `origin`.\n- The key scope/ref suffix should match the local GitMeta name for agentlog.\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- Should GitButler web/review infrastructure materialize the same agentlog key\n  scope directly, or should a backend ingest it into another store after Git\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T16:47:35.557Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}